news.title: PNB Housing Finance net profit rises 23.83% in Q2 FY26
news.para: PNB Housing Finance reported a robust 23.83% year-on-year growth in net consolidated profit for Q2 FY26, reaching ₹581.59 crore. The company's total income also saw a 13.35% increase. PNB Housing Finance is focusing on accelerating retail growth and expanding its affordable and emerging markets segment footprint.

news.title: Delhi: Residents barred from complaining against flat quality, design of DDA's premium housing scheme
news.para: Delhi Development Authority's Towering Heights housing scheme in East Delhi will not accept complaints regarding flat defects. This premium housing project offers 1,026 flats starting at Rs 1.78 crore. Construction is expected to be ready by July 2026. Successful bidders will pay 75 percent at e-auction and the rest by possession.

news.title: Elon Musk’s Starlink Satellite leases office space in Mumbai’s Chandivali
news.para: Elon Musk's Starlink has leased office space in Mumbai's Chandivali. This move marks a significant step in the company's India rollout plans. Starlink is preparing to launch its satellite communication services across the country. Mumbai is expected to be a key hub for its operations.

news.title: Suraj Estate Developers' net profit up 3.96% in Q2 FY26
news.para: Suraj Estate Developers announced strong financial results for the quarter ending September 30, 2025. The company saw its net profit grow by 3.96 percent. Total income also experienced a significant increase of 32.65 percent. The board also approved a postal ballot to seek shareholder approval for the appointment of Ananta Singh Raghuvanshi as an independent director.

news.title: Mumbai: Original owners of Sanjan bungalow oppose sale
news.para: Original owners of a Sanjan bungalow are vehemently opposing its sale by the World Zoroastrian Organisation Trust Funds. The Davierwalla family sold the property at a below-market rate in 1997, stipulating it be used solely for Parsi-Irani community welfare.  Concerns are raised about commercial exploitation, with a community group offering to buy it to keep it within the fold.

news.title: Della Group eyes ₹700 crore revenue, ₹450 crore EBITDA by FY27
news.para: Della Group projects a significant revenue surge to ₹700 crore by FY27, driven by a new proprietary real estate model and expansion into integrated townships. This shift from its Lonavala resort operations, which generated ₹200 crore in FY25, aims to unlock higher value for partners through an end-to-end CDDMO framework.

news.title: Controversy erupts over Indore civic body property survey, mayor suspends drive till SOP is ready
news.para: A property tax survey by the Indore Municipal Corporation sparked a major controversy, leading to a standoff at a police station and multiple FIRs. High-level political intervention followed, with a cabinet minister calling for a resolution. The mayor has since halted the survey, promising a new Standard Operating Procedure and public appeal for property assessment corrections.

news.title: Shriram Properties to jointly develop row housing project in Yelahanka, Bengaluru
news.para: Shriram Properties has entered a joint development agreement for seven acres in North Bengaluru. This land will be used to develop row houses. The project has an estimated gross development value of ₹600 crore. The company is focusing on partnerships for growth. Yelahanka's infrastructure and proximity to a biodiversity park make it a prime location for premium homes.

news.title: Goa housing board gets nod for legal, IT wings
news.para: Goa's state cabinet has approved the establishment of a legal and IT cell within the Goa Housing Board (GHB), creating 11 new posts. This move aims to bolster the board's capacity to provide affordable housing and manage its operations. The GHB, a self-sustaining statutory body, will now enhance its legal and technological infrastructure.

news.title: Telangana: TRSCL to conduct e-auction of plots from October 28
news.para: Telangana Rajiv Swagruha Corporation Limited is holding an e-auction for open plots in Kurmalguda, Thorrur, and Bahadurpally from October 28-30. Plot sizes vary, with upset prices ranging from ₹20,000 to ₹30,000 per square yard. The auction will be conducted in multiple sessions across the three days.

news.title: SC issues notice to CBI on bail plea of former DHFL promoter
news.para: The Supreme Court is now deliberating on a bail request from Kapil Wadhawan, former head of DHFL, embroiled in a colossal banking fraud scandal that has allegedly siphoned off Rs 34,926 crore. The Delhi High Court has already rebuffed Wadhawan's plea, emphasizing his problematic conduct in jail and the grave severity of the charges against him.

news.title: Pune: Builder asks Jain trust to cancel deal
news.para: In a surprising turn of events, a prominent builder in Pune has opted to back out of a lucrative deal involving a property held by a Jain trust. Citing the emergence of unfounded rumors and significant public outcry, the builder emphasized his decision was rooted in a sense of ethical obligation towards the Jain community.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation to revive Poonkulam housing project after 17-year delay
news.para: Thiruvananthapuram City Corporation is restarting a stalled housing project at Poonkulam. The project, originally for underprivileged families, faced financial issues and delays. Now, it will house 32 families. A stability audit is complete, and a new tender will be floated soon. Basic facilities will be included. Construction is expected to take 18 to 24 months.

news.title: Khadki cantonment board to crack down on commercial use of public properties
news.para: The Khadki Cantonment Board is cracking down on the misuse of public properties. Facilities like marriage halls and gyms, built for residents, are being commercially exploited. The board will take strict action against violators. This move aims to ensure public facilities benefit the community as intended. Residents welcome the decision, hoping for accessible services.

news.title: Chennai-grown portal Findbhk.com challenges national rivals with 90% retention
news.para: A homegrown real estate portal, Findbhk, is revolutionizing Chennai's property market. It partners with local builders, offering a focused search experience for buyers.  This approach ensures quality leads and high developer satisfaction.  Findbhk is now expanding to Coimbatore, aiming to replicate its success in another key real estate hub.

news.title: How technology is redefining commercial interior design: Flipspaces’ VR & visualization tools
news.para: Flipspaces is transforming commercial interior design. Using Virtual Reality and AI, the company lets clients visualize office spaces before construction. This tech-first approach reduces errors and project delays. With significant funding, Flipspaces is expanding globally, offering end-to-end interior solutions. Their innovative methods create functional and inspiring workspaces for modern businesses.

news.title: FIRs set to be filed against 214 in Gurugram over illegal housing colonies & eateries
news.para: District town planner recommends 15 FIRs against 214 individuals for illegal colonies, unauthorized dhabas, and warehouses. Violations include illegal plotting on 23.55 acres and commercial activities in restricted zones, impacting areas like Pataudi and Farrukhnagar. These actions follow ignored restoration orders and demolition drives.

news.title: Pune: Cluster redevelopment of old wadas stuck in policy hurdles & opposition from residents
news.para: Pune's cluster development initiative, proposed eight years ago to redevelop old wadas and buildings, has seen minimal progress due to challenges in consolidating land and securing owner/tenant consent. Residents of aging housing societies face infrastructure issues, while policymakers struggle to accelerate reconstruction efforts.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt backs Noida authority's move to cancel 29 plots lying idle for two decades
news.para: Uttar Pradesh industrial development department has upheld Noida Authority's decision to cancel land allotments for 29 industrial units. The department dismissed a revision petition from Elevator IT Solutions Ltd, which challenged the cancellation for failing to commence construction despite repeated extensions and statutory relaxations.

news.title: Delhi may get ‘A+’ property zone as government reviews circle rates for Lutyens’ area, farmhouses
news.para: Delhi government is reviewing suggestions to revise circle rates, including a new 'A+' category for premium Lutyens' Delhi areas and an overhaul of farmhouse rates. Proposed biennial reviews and greater data transparency aim to align rates with market realities, boost revenue, and enhance investor confidence.
